burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames

Class SGAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.SGAgent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EquilibriumPlayingSGAgent, GrimTrigger, LearningAgentToSGAgentInterface, MultiAgentDPPlanningAgent, MultiAgentQLearning, RandomSGAgent, SetStrategySGAgent, SGNaiveQLAgent, TitForTat

    public abstract class SGAgent
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class defines the the shell code and interface for creating agents that can make decisions in mutli-agent stochastic game worlds. Agents have names to identify themselves and can joint multi-agent worlds as a specific type of agent that is specified by their SGAgentType. Agents are informed by the world when a game is starting and ending and they are also queried by the world for the action they will take. After all agents in the world have chosen their action, the world changes and informs each agent of the outcome for all agents in the world.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan
